<p>Let's say I have the following JiBX mapping:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt; &lt;binding name="VehicleEnquiry" direction="output"&gt;   &lt;mapping name="Request" class="com.example.Request"&gt;     &lt;structure name="Body" flexible="true" ordered="false"&gt;       &lt;structure name="Params" flexible="true" ordered="false"&gt;         &lt;value name="Synchronous" get-method="getSynchronousIndicator" usage="optional"/&gt;         &lt;collection name="Boats" field="boats" usage="optional"/&gt;         &lt;collection name="Vehicles" field="vehicles" usage="optional"/&gt;       &lt;/structure&gt;     &lt;/structure&gt;   &lt;/mapping&gt;   &lt;mapping name="BoatSearch" class="com.example.Pair"&gt;     &lt;value name="Rego" get-method="getRegistration" usage="optional"/&gt;     &lt;value name="Licensed" get-method="isLicensed" usage="optional"/&gt;   &lt;/mapping&gt;   &lt;mapping name="VehicleSearch" class="com.example.Pair"&gt;     &lt;value name="License" get-method="getLicense" usage="optional"/&gt;     &lt;value name="Registered" get-method="isRegistered" usage="optional"/&gt;   &lt;/mapping&gt; &lt;/binding&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Whereby inside my enquiry's params section, I can specify a list of boats or vehicles I want to enquire about. Due to the nature of those structures, they can both be easily represented using a standard Pair object. </p>  <p>Problem is, when I run the JiBX binding compiler it tells me that:</p>  <p><em>Conflicting mappings for class com.example.Pair</em></p>  <p>Why is it unable to re-use the same object for two similar structures? It would seem overhead to have to create BoatSearch and VehicleSearch objects if they were both essentially just Pairs.</p>